IN	Spiced matzo chips
IN	1 (8-10 inch) English cucumber, peeled
IN	3-4 heads Belgian endive, separated into leaves
IN	1/8 cup fresh mint leaves (discard stems)
IN	1/4 cup flat-leaf Italian parsley leaves (discard stems)
IN	1 cup small grape or cherry tomatoes, quartered
IN	1 cup arugula
IN	Juice of 1 lemon
IN	4 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil
IN	1 clove fresh garlic, minced
IN	Pinch of coarse sea salt or kosher salt
IN	1/2 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper
PR	Prepare the matzo chips .
PR	Slice the cucumbers in half lengthwise. With a spoon, scoop out and discard the pulp. Chop into 1/2-inch pieces. Place into a large salad bowl.
PR	Thinly slice the endive and place into the bowl. Lay the mint leaves in a pile and tear them; they will bruise if you cut them with a knife. Add to the bowl. Toss in the parsley, tomatoes, and arugula. Mix in the lemon juice, olive oil, and garlic. Season with salt and pepper, tossing to combine. Allow to marinate for a few minutes.
PR	Stand 2 matzo chips in each salad.
